{{!
    Mustache template for rendering the edit page in the filter_autotranslate plugin.

    Purpose:
    This template renders the edit page, displaying a form for editing a translation alongside
    the source text for reference. It uses a two-column layout to present the form and source text
    side by side.

    Variables:
    - form: HTML for the edit form (rendered by edit_form.php).
    - source_text: The source text (lang = 'other') for the translation.
    - source_text_label: The label for the source text section (e.g., "Source Text").

    Design Decisions:
    - Uses Bootstrap classes (row, col-md-7, col-md-5, card) for a responsive two-column layout.
    - Places the edit form on the left (7 columns) and the source text on the right (5 columns)
      to provide context while editing.
    - Includes card titles for clarity and visual separation.

    @template
    {
        "form": "<form action=\"edit.php\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"text\" name=\"translated_text\" value=\"Hello world\" /></form>",
        "source_text": "Hola mundo",
        "source_text_label": "Source Text"
    }
}}
<div class="row mb-3">
    <div class="col-md-7">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">{{#str}}translation, filter_autotranslate{{/str}}</h5>
                {{{form}}}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="card-title">{{source_text_label}}{{^source_text_label}}{{#str}}sourcetext, filter_autotranslate{{/str}}{{/source_text_label}}</h5>
                <div class="card-text">
                    {{{source_text}}}
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>